cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.SE, cs.DS

This paper deals with the semantics of non-deterministic functions in functional logic languages, which is a topic closely related to programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO). The paper proposes an extension to existing languages, which involves formal operational calculi (cs.FL) and implementation (cs.SE). Finally, the paper uses the system Toy, which is a tool for exploring the semantics of programming languages, and thus could be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
